## Architecture Built

```
hrv-agent/
├── data/
│   ├── models.py          ← Pydantic v2 — all 59 HRV fields w/ aliases + validators
│   ├── loader.py          ← HRVClinicalLoader — validation, stats, feature groups
│   └── vector_store.py    ← LanceDB + Titan Embeddings hybrid RAG
├── ml/
│   ├── features.py        ← Composite risk score + 4 interaction features
│   ├── classifier.py      ← XGBoost + isotonic calibration + risk stratification
│   └── trainer.py         ← SMOTE + 80/20 split + threshold optimization + metrics
├── agents/
│   ├── state.py           ← HRVAgentState TypedDict
│   ├── graph.py           ← LangGraph StateGraph (8 nodes, conditional routing)
│   └── nodes/
│       ├── validation.py              ← Schema + physiological sanity checks
│       ├── feature_analysis.py        ← Group-level HRV summaries
│       ├── anomaly_detection.py       ← 10 hard clinical thresholds (no LLM)
│       ├── ml_scoring.py              ← XGBoost inference + heuristic fallback
│       ├── rag_retrieval.py           ← LanceDB cosine search (skipped in quick mode)
│       ├── clinical_interpretation.py ← Claude Sonnet + deterministic fallback
│       ├── recommendation.py          ← Sonnet + 4-tier template fallback
│       └── synthesis.py               ← Final briefing + cost tracking
├── tools/hrv_tools.py     ← 5 MCP tools (similarity search, risk calc, etc.)
├── bedrock/
│   ├── client.py          ← Lazy-loaded Sonnet + Haiku + Titan, retry decorator
│   └── prompts.py         ← System prompts per node
├── api/
│   ├── main.py            ← FastAPI + Mangum Lambda adapter + startup pre-warming
│   ├── auth.py            ← X-API-Key auth
│   └── routes/
│       ├── analyze.py     ← POST /analyze/single, /analyze/batch
│       ├── chat.py        ← POST /chat (conversational coach)
│       └── metrics.py     ← GET /model/metrics, /metrics, /similar/{id}, /health
├── observability/
│   ├── telemetry.py       ← NodeTelemetry + PipelineTelemetry + ring buffer
│   └── evaluation.py      ← Metrics save/load
├── tests/                 ← 18 unit tests (all passing)
├── Dockerfile             ← Multi-stage build
├── docker-compose.yml     ← Persistent volumes for model + LanceDB
└── .github/workflows/deploy.yml ← CI: ruff + mypy + pytest + Docker build
```

---

## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| Threshold optimization in training | Maximizes recall (clinical priority: minimize missed sepsis) |
| SMOTE at threshold 0.50 (not data level) | Preserves calibration accuracy; SMOTE happens on features |
| Lazy Bedrock loading | API and agents work without AWS credentials (graceful degradation) |
| Heuristic fallback in every node | System is runnable without Bedrock for development/testing |
| LangGraph conditional routing | "quick" mode skips RAG; critical anomalies expedite pipeline |
| `scale_pos_weight=7.0` + SMOTE | Double-handles 87.5/12.5 imbalance for maximum robustness |

---

## To Run the System

### Quick Start (virtual env with existing .venv)
```bash
cd /Users/yashnayi/Desktop/HRV/hrv-agent

# Train model (already done — ml/models/xgb_hrv_v1.pkl exists)
PYTHONPATH=. /Users/yashnayi/Desktop/HRV/.venv/bin/python ml/trainer.py \
  "../HRV data 20201209 2.xlsx" ml/models/xgb_hrv_v1.pkl

# Run tests
PYTHONPATH=. /Users/yashnayi/Desktop/HRV/.venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/ -v

# Run API (requires AWS credentials for Bedrock; runs in degraded mode without)
cp .env.example .env  # fill in AWS keys
PYTHONPATH=. /Users/yashnayi/Desktop/HRV/.venv/bin/python api/main.py
```

### Docker
```bash
cp .env.example .env  # fill in AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID, AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY, HRV_API_KEY
docker-compose up --build
# API available at http://localhost:8000/docs
```

### Next steps to complete activation
1. **Fill in `.env`** with your AWS credentials (Bedrock access needed for Claude 3 LLMs)
2. **Populate LanceDB**: run `data/vector_store.py` to embed and index the 4,314 records
3. **Deploy**: push to GitHub → CI/CD builds and validates Docker image automatically
